The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Mixed bag from Tata Tea 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Mixed bag from Tata Tea 
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, July 28: Tata Tea Ltd has reported a 12 per cent rise in consolidated income from worldwide operations at Rs 1,134.69 crore during the first quarter of 2008-09 compared with Rs 1,010.74 in the corresponding quarter of the previous year.        
	While consolidated net profit jumped 75 per cent to Rs 85.39 crore from Rs 48.93 crore, the standalone net profit dipped to Rs 37.71 crore from Rs 41.23 crore in the year-ago period.        
	During the quarter under review, the company had to make a provision of Rs 2.2 crore under a employee separation scheme.        
	A company spokesperson said profits had been impacted by an increase in the prices of raw materials and a higher expenditure on adverstisements during the quarter.        
	Standalone income during the first quarter rose 12 per cent to Rs 314.97 crore from Rs 280.61 crore a year ago.         
	A strong show in branded tea helped improve the companys domestic performance.        
	During the quarter, Tata Teas holding in Tetley Group increased to 78.79 per cent from 77.78 per cent following the conversion of loans into equity shares.                                                                                                                                      
